==English==

===Etymology===
From [[sight]] + [[see]] + [[-ing]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-sightseeing.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
'''sightseeing'''
#Relating to or having the purpose of seeing points of interest
#:''They went on a '''sightseeing''' trip around the area.''

===Noun===
'''sightseeing'''
#The practice of going out looking at things; [[tourism]].
#:''Sightseeing is a frequent reason to visit San Francisco.''

===Verb===
'''sightseeing'''
#[[touring|Touring]]; visiting places for the purpose of seeing them.
#:''Would you like to go '''sightseeing''' with me someday?''

